ex.php?title=Trial_by_media&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.pbs.org/newshour/spc/bb/media/july-dec98/lawyers_10-19a.html\">\"Legal News: News Hour with Jim Lehrer\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Transcript)</span>. Public Broadcasting System (PBS). 19 October 1998<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">12 March</span> 2011</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Legal+News%3A+News+Hour+with+Jim+Lehrer&amp;rft.pub=Public+Broadcasting+System+%28PBS%29&amp;rft.date=1998-10-19&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fnewshour%2Fspc%2Fbb%2Fmedia%2Fjuly-dec98%2Flawyers_10-19a.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATrial+by+media\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Bowcott, Owen (5 July 2011). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/law/2011/jul/05/contempt-court-rules-trial-media\">\"Contempt of court rules are designed to avoid trial by media\"</a>. <i>The Guardian</i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Guardian&amp;rft.atitle=Contempt+of+court+rules+are+designed+to+avoid+trial+by+media&amp;rft.date=2011-07-05&amp;rft.aulast=Bowcott&amp;rft.aufirst=Owen&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Flaw%2F2011%2Fjul%2F05%2Fcontempt-court-rules-trial-media&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATrial+by+media\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Trial_by_media&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://judis.nic.in/andhra/qrydisp.asp?tfnm=832\">Condemnation of trial by media</a>. Complete text of the judgement by the Andhra Pradesh High Court, India.</li></ul>\n<p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Authority_control_frameless_&amp;#124;text-top_&amp;#124;10px_&amp;#124;alt=Edit_this_at_Wikidata_&amp;#124;link=https&amp;#58;//www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q3269491&amp;#124;Edit_this_at_Wikidata\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks hlist navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit\"><tbody><tr><th id=\"Authority_control_frameless_&amp;#124;text-top_&amp;#124;10px_&amp;#124;alt=Edit_this_at_Wikidata_&amp;#124;link=https&amp;#58;//www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q3269491&amp;#124;Edit_this_at_Wikidata\" scope=\"row\" class=\"navbox-group\" style=\"width:1%\"><a href=\"/wiki/Help:Authority_control\" title=\"Help:Authority control\">Authority control</a> <a href=\"https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q3269491\" title=\"Edit this at Wikidata\"><img alt=\"Edit this at Wikidata\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Blue_pencil.svg/10px-Blue_pencil.svg.png\" width=\"10\" height=\"10\" style=\"vertical-align: text-top\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/